  "title": "Iggy Beamish Destroys Traditional Marriage",
  "description": "★★★★1/2 \"Delightful train wreck you can't help but root for.\" (Reviews Hub Dublin) ★★★★ \"Journey of hilarious humiliations.\" (Edmonton Journal) From the creator of last year's sold-out smash hit THE HETEROSEXUALS! Iggy Beamish makes a dubious living officiating straight weddings while avoiding the reality of his own gay divorce.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Johnnie McNamara Walker<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Byron LaViolette<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Johnnie McNamara Walker<br/>",
  "website": "https://johnniemcnamarawalker.com | @handsomejohnnie",
  "plain_language": "Iggy Beamish Destroys Traditional Marriage is a solo play written and performed by Johnnie McNamara Walker. It tells the story of Iggy Beamish, who has a job officiating weddings for straight people but hides from the reality of his own gay divorce. As Iggy struggles to make a living, find somewhere to live, and get over his ex, he makes a series of hilarious friends and enemies while exploring Toronto's queer nightlife, real estate market, and wedding industrial complex.",
